19/07/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Newly-appointed US Ambassador to Romania Jack Crouch presented his credentials to President Ion Iliescu on Friday (16 July). 
At his first news conference in Bucharest, Crouch stressed US support for Romania and vowed to help create an attractive business environment there. 
The US Senate confirmed Crouch's appointment in late May.
In other news, Romanian Prime Minister Adrian Nastase left for New York on Sunday. 
He will oversee a meeting of the UN Security Council, whose rotating presidency Romania currently holds. 
Later in the week, he will meet with top US officials, including President George W. 
Bush. 
(Rompres, Mediafax - 16/07/04)
